io.branch.referral

Class RemoteInterface

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.branch.referral.RemoteInterface
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BranchRemoteInterface

    public class RemoteInterface
extends java.lang.Object

    This class assists with RESTful calls to the Branch API, by encapsulating a generic HttpClient object, and handling all restful calls via one of its GET or POST capable methods.

    • Method Detail

      • make_restful_get

        public ServerResponse make_restful_get(java.lang.String url,
                                       java.lang.String tag,
                                       int timeout)

        Make a RESTful GET request, by calling make_restful_get(String, String, int, boolean) with the logging Boolean parameter pre-populated.

        Parameters:
        url - A String URL to request from.
        tag - A String tag for logging/analytics purposes.
        timeout - An Integer value containing the number of milliseconds to wait before considering a server request to have timed out.
        Returns:
        A ServerResponse object containing the result of the RESTful request.

      • make_restful_get

        public ServerResponse make_restful_get(java.lang.String url,
                                       java.lang.String tag,
                                       int timeout,
                                       boolean log)

        The main RESTful GET method; the other one (make_restful_get(String, String, int)) calls this one with a pre-populated logging parameter.

        Parameters:
        url - A String URL to request from.
        tag - A String tag for logging/analytics purposes.
        timeout - An Integer value containing the number of milliseconds to wait before considering a server request to have timed out.
        log - A Boolean value that specifies whether debug logging should be enabled for this request or not.
        Returns:
        A ServerResponse object containing the result of the RESTful request.

      • make_restful_post

        public ServerResponse make_restful_post(JSONObject body,
                                        java.lang.String url,
                                        java.lang.String tag,
                                        int timeout)

        Makes a RESTful POST call with logging enabled, without an associated data dictionary; passed as null.

        Parameters:
        body - A JSONObject containing the main data body/payload of the request.
        url - A String URL to request from.
        tag - A String tag for logging/analytics purposes.
        timeout - An Integer value containing the number of milliseconds to wait before considering a server request to have timed out.
        Returns:
        A ServerResponse object representing the HttpEntity response in Branch SDK terms.

      • make_restful_post

        public ServerResponse make_restful_post(JSONObject body,
                                        java.lang.String url,
                                        java.lang.String tag,
                                        int timeout,
                                        BranchLinkData linkData)

        Makes a RESTful POST call with logging enabled.

        Parameters:
        body - A JSONObject containing the main data body/payload of the request.
        url - A String URL to request from.
        tag - A String tag for logging/analytics purposes.
        timeout - An Integer value containing the number of milliseconds to wait before considering a server request to have timed out.
        linkData - A BranchLinkData object containing the data dictionary associated with the link subject of the original server request.
        Returns:
        A ServerResponse object representing the HttpEntity response in Branch SDK terms.
